=== Spatial planning ===
Aalen forms a ''Mittelzentrum'' (“medium-level centre”) within the [[Ostwürttemberg]] region. It’s designated [[catchment area (human geography)|catchment area]] includes the following municipalities of the central and eastern Ostalbkreis district: [[Abtsgmünd]], [[Bopfingen]], [[Essingen (Württemberg)|Essingen]], [[Hüttlingen (Württemberg)|Hüttlingen]], [[Kirchheim am Ries]], [[Lauchheim]], [[Neresheim]], [[Oberkochen]], [[Riesbürg]] and [[Westhausen (Württemberg)|Westhausen]], and is interwoven with the catchment area of [[Nördlingen]], situated in [[Bavaria]], {{convert|30|km|mi}} east of Aalen.

=== Climate ===
As Aalen’s territory sprawls on escarpments of the Swabian Jura, on the Albuch and the Härtsfeld landscapes, and its elevation has a range of {{convert|355|m|ft}}, the climate varies from district to district.

The [[weather station]] the following data originate from is located between the town centre and Wasseralfingen at about {{Coord|48|51|02|N|10|05|44|E|name=weather station|display=inline}} and has been in operation since 1991.

The sunshine duration is about 1800 hours per year, which averages 4.93 hours per day. So Aalen is above the German average of 1550 hours per year. However, with 167 days of [[precipitation (meteorology)|precipitation]], Aalen’s region also ranks above the German average of 138. The annual rainfall is {{convert|807|mm|in}}, which places Aalen in the middle within Baden-Württemberg.<ref>State Institute for Environment, Measurements and Nature Conservation Baden-Württemberg (2013)</ref>
The annual mean temperature is {{convert|9.9|C|F}}. Here Aalen ranks above the German average of {{convert|8.2|C|F}} and the Baden-Württemberg average of {{convert|8.1|C|F}}.

